  "prompt": "Who are the best 5 left handed fast bowlers in Indian domestic cricket after Zaheer Khan's retirement?",
  "response": "After Zaheer Khan's retirement from international cricket, several left-handed fast bowlers have made a significant impact in Indian domestic cricket. Here are five of the best left-handed fast bowlers in Indian domestic cricket post-Zaheer Khan:\n\n1. **Mustafizur Rahman** (though primarily representing Bangladesh, he has played in the IPL and had a notable impact in Indian domestic leagues as well).\n  \n2. **Jaydev Unadkat** - Unadkat has been a consistent performer in domestic cricket, especially in the Ranji Trophy, and has also made appearances in the IPL.\n\n3. **Khaleel Ahmed** - Known for his left-arm pace, Khaleel has been a regular feature in domestic cricket and has played for India in limited-overs formats.\n\n4. **Shivam Dube** - Primarily known as an all-rounder, Dube has also shown his capabilities as a left-arm fast bowler in domestic competitions.\n\n5. **Vaibhav Arora** - Emerging as a promising left-arm pacer, Arora has been recognized for his performances in domestic cricket, particularly in the Ranji Trophy and has made headlines in the IPL as well.\n\nThese bowlers represent a blend of experience and youthful talent, showcasing the potential of left-handed fast bowlers in Indian domestic circuits since Zaheer Khan's era.",
